{"title_page": "College of Health Care Professions", "text_new": "{{advert|date=May 2017}}\n{{Infobox university\n|name            = The College of Health Care Professions (CHCP)\n|established     = 1988\n|type            = Private, for-profit\n|city            = [[Houston]]\n|state           = Texas\n|country         = United States\n|campus          = 7 campuses throughout the state\n|website         = {{URL|http://www.chcp.edu/}}\n|logo            = \n|former_name     = The Academy of Health Care Professions\n}}\n\nThe '''College of Health Care Professions''' ('''CHCP''') is a private [[For-profit higher education in the United States|for-profit school]] of [[allied health professions]] with its headquarters in [[Houston]], [[Texas]], and multiple campuses throughout the state.\n\n==History==  \nIn 1988, the physicians of MacGregor Medical Association, a physician\u2019s practice of [[Texas Medical Center]], founded the Academy of Health Care Professions. Its purpose was to provide quality training of allied health staff in-house, to support MacGregor\u2019s growth. In 1990, the academy was approved by the [[Texas Workforce Commission]] to provide allied health education and training. In 2012, the Academy of Health Care Professions was renamed The College of Health Care Professions (CHCP).<ref>{{cite web|title=College of Health Care Professions History|url=http://www.chcp.edu/why-chcp/history|website=CHCP|accessdate=22 August 2016}}</ref>\n\n==Accreditation==\nCHCP is accredited by the [[Accrediting Bureau of Health Education Schools]] (ABHES).<ref>{{cite web|title=ABHES Directory of Schools|url=https://ams.abhes.org/ams/onlineDirectory/pages/directory.aspx|website=ABHES|accessdate=22 August 2016|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20160812213307/https://ams.abhes.org/ams/onlineDirectory/pages/directory.aspx|archive-date=12 August 2016|url-status=dead}}</ref>\n\n==References==\n{{Reflist}}\n\n==External links==\n* [http://www.chcp.edu/ Official website]\n\n{{